    "short_description": "Steamboats, antiques, craft beer, and some of KC's best casual eats along the Missouri River.",
    "long_description": "Kansas City's River Market neighborhood sits at the original heart of the city, where settlers and traders first arrived along the Missouri River in the 19th century. Today it's one of KC's most walkable and eclectic neighborhoods, blending history, food, and nightlife into a compact area just north of downtown. Start the day with breakfast at The Farmhouse, a farm-to-table spot beloved for its weekend brunch, or grab a bite at Habashi House, a River Market institution known for its Mediterranean and Middle Eastern fare. The Arabia Steamboat Museum is a must-see — it houses the remarkably preserved cargo of a steamboat that sank in the Missouri in 1856, recovered entirely intact over a century later. Antique hunters will lose track of time at River Market Antiques, a massive multi-dealer mall full of vintage finds. For dinner, Enzo offers Italian-inspired plates in a relaxed setting. Cap the evening with craft beers at Strange Days Brewing Co. or River Bluff Brewing, two excellent taprooms that anchor the neighborhood's growing beer scene.",
